{
  "stem": "4189.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they sent this train directly to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Now, we, we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We had no idea about Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had never heard about such a place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So we-- the group that came from France, all those men, that was a group of about 300 that came from France.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The others were from-- were the women and the children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That whole transport consisted of 848 men and 94 women and 41 children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And from this entire transport, we found out now through the official records, that only 54 men survived from the entire transport of 840 more people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now when the train arrived in Auschwitz, they opened the doors of the cars and everybody out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], they yelled at us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And right away they said that the women and the children had to go to one side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all the men had to go to another side.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we notice in the background, we noticed that there were some people that were working there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they looked kind of funny to us because they had their head shaven.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had no hair.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were wearing these uniforms, like pajamas with stripes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what they were doing, they were taking the luggage off the trains, the little bit of luggage what we had from France.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That came from France, we had hardly any luggage because we came from a labor camp from France, and we had very little personal belongings.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everything we had that was of value was already taken away from us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the people that came from Brussels now, from [NON-ENGLISH], they had suitcases with their personal belongings.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And all that was taken away from them.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
